answers.body_markdown:
1. Consider using DB connection pool such as [Hikari][1] or [C3P0][2] (both available at Maven Repository). Opening a connection every time is very inefficient and you may run out of connections which may be the error you are getting.  Please post your error.
2. Use try-with-resources instead of doing the finally block.  It will automatically call close() on Autoclosable objects such as Connection, Statement, PreparedStatement, ResultSet, etc.


&gt;     try (
&gt;         Connection myConnection = MyConnectionPool.getConnection();
&gt;         Statement stmt = myConnection.createStatement();
&gt;         ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery(query)
&gt;     ) {
&gt;         // Do work with rs
&gt;     }



  [1]: https://github.com/brettwooldridge/HikariCP
  [2]: https://www.mchange.com/projects/c3p0/

